Jonasson et al 4 ), few studies have explored the cognitive effects of dance-exercise intervention (DI), with variable methods and inconclusive results. 5 Moreover, the DI impact on the ageing brain structure is not well understood.
Therefore, we designed a randomized controlled trial in order to shed further light on the effects of an optimized, structured sixmonth DI as compared to lifestyle activities as usual in cognitively well-characterized senior individuals without dementia.
